jenes.tutorials.old.problem5

Class DoubleAlleleSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • jenes.chromosome.GenericAlleleSet<java.lang.Double>
      • jenes.tutorials.old.problem5.DoubleAlleleSet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AlleleSet<java.lang.Double>

    public class DoubleAlleleSet
extends GenericAlleleSet<java.lang.Double>
    Tutorial illustrating the use of object-oriented chromosomes, whose allele set can be defined by the user for each gene. In this example the chromosomes are combinations of colors. We aim at finding the vector of colors closest to a given sequence. This class defines an allele set made of doubles.
